{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Quick Backchannel Response Card for Quick Practice Hub",
  "description": "Add a new frontend-only mini-drill card 'Quick Backchannel' that trains learners to produce natural English listener-feedback signals (uh-huh, really?, oh no!, that's great!, no way!, makes sense, etc.) — a critical conversational micro-skill not yet covered by any existing card. Implementation:\n\n1. Create new component `frontend/src/components/QuickBackchannelCard.tsx`. It contains a static, in-file bank of ~20 short speaker utterances grouped by emotional context (good news, bad news, surprise, agreement, mild disbelief, sympathy), each with 3-4 acceptable backchannel responses. Example item: { speaker: \"I just got promoted at work!\", context: 'good_news', accepted: ['Congratulations!', 'That\\'s great!', 'Awesome!', 'Nice!'] }.\n\n2. Flow per round: (a) auto-play the speaker utterance via `speechSynthesis` (reuse the same TTS pattern used in `QuickListenRespondCard.tsx` / `QuickShadowCard.tsx` — voice selection, rate slider, replay button), (b) show a small context badge after first playback (e.g. 🎉 Good news), (c) user picks one of 4 multiple-choice backchannel buttons (3 from the accepted list shuffled with 1 distractor pulled from a wrong-context category), (d) immediate feedback — green check + brief explanation if correct, red X + show all accepted responses if wrong, (e) optional 'Say it' button that uses Web Speech Recognition (when available, like `QuickSpeakCard`) to let user voice the chosen reply and shows a match indicator (case-insensitive substring against any accepted response). Skip gracefully if recognition unavailable.\n\n3. Round counter (5 rounds per session), score tally, and a final summary screen with 'Try again' and 'Back to hub' buttons mirroring the layout of `QuickQuestionFormationCard.tsx`.\n\n4. Register the card in `frontend/src/components/QuickPracticeHub.tsx`: add an entry to the cards array with id `backchannel`, an appropriate icon/emoji (💬), Japanese + English labels (e.g. 'あいづち練習' / 'Backchannel'), the listening+speaking tags so it appears in existing tag filters, and wire it into the favorites flow already used by sibling cards.\n\n5. Add a basic unit test `frontend/src/__tests__/QuickBackchannelCard.test.tsx` (mock `speechSynthesis`) verifying: card renders, replay button triggers TTS, selecting a correct response shows positive feedback and increments score, selecting a distractor shows the accepted answer list, completing 5 rounds shows the summary.\n\nNo backend, DB, or API changes — purely frontend with a static prompt bank, so it ships in one iteration. Adds a genuinely fresh conversational-listening skill distinct from recently shipped reverse-translation, question-formation, reply-hints, and shadowing cards.",
  "files_to_modify": ["frontend/src/components/QuickBackchannelCard.tsx", "frontend/src/components/QuickPracticeHub.tsx", "frontend/src/__tests__/QuickBackchannelCard.test.tsx"],
