{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Pronunciation result: word-level heatmap with tap-to-drill on missed words",
  "description": "After a shadowing attempt on the Pronunciation page, the API already returns per-word evaluation in `PronunciationFeedback.word_feedback` (each entry has `expected`, `heard`, `is_correct`, `tip`, optional `phoneme_issues`). Currently the result phase shows aggregate score + a flat list of feedback, missing an at-a-glance view of which specific words the user nailed vs. flubbed and offering no immediate way to retry just those words.\n\nAdd a new component `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/WordHeatmap.tsx` that renders the reference sentence as inline tokens, each colored by its `is_correct` state (green for correct, amber/red for missed, neutral grey for words not aligned). Each missed word is a button: clicking it expands a small inline panel with: (1) the `tip` text and any `phoneme_issues` (target/produced/position), (2) a 🔊 button that calls `tts.speak(word)` to model the word in isolation, and (3) a 🎤 retry button that uses `useSpeechRecognition` to capture a single repeat (up to 3 attempts, reusing the `normalizeWord` and `transcriptMatches` helpers exported from `MissedWordDrill.tsx`). On a successful match show a ✓ check and dim the panel; on failure show the heard transcript with a hint to try again. No backend changes — purely a richer frontend rendering of existing data.\n\nIntegration: in `frontend/src/pages/Pronunciation.tsx`, in the `phase === 'result'` block where `feedback` is rendered (shadowing mode), insert `<WordHeatmap referenceText={selectedSentence} wordFeedback={feedback.word_feedback} tts={tts} />` above the existing feedback list. Keep the existing aggregate score, focus areas, and `MissedWordDrill` button unchanged so the cross-session trouble-words flow still works; the heatmap targets the *current* attempt only.\n\nExport `WordHeatmap` from `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/index.ts`. Add a focused unit test file `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/__tests__/WordHeatmap.test.tsx` that verifies: (a) tokens render with correct color class based on `is_correct`, (b) clicking a missed word reveals its `tip` and the retry button, (c) when the SpeechRecognition mock returns a matching transcript the word is marked as resolved (uses the same matcher semantics as `transcriptMatches`).\n\nThis strengthens the existing Pronunciation flow with immediate, targeted repair practice — turning each shadowing attempt into a self-contained diagnose→drill loop without leaving the page, and reusing existing infrastructure (TTS hook, speech recognition hook, MissedWordDrill matchers).",
