  "title": "Vocabulary Leech Words panel — surface stubborn words for focused drilling",
  "description": "The Vocabulary page surfaces SRS due words and progress, but never highlights 'leech' words — words a user repeatedly gets wrong despite reviews. The schema already tracks per-word incorrect_count and correct_count in vocabulary_progress (no migration needed), so we can ship this in one iteration.\n\nWhat to build:\n\n1. Backend DAL — add `get_leech_words(limit: int = 10)` to `app/dal/vocabulary.py`. A 'leech' is defined as a word with `incorrect_count >= 3` AND `incorrect_count >= correct_count` AND `level <= 2` (i.e. user has tried it several times, still failing, hasn't graduated). Return joined rows with word, meaning, example_sentence, topic, correct_count, incorrect_count, level, and a derived `miss_rate = incorrect / (correct + incorrect)`. Order by miss_rate DESC then incorrect_count DESC. Skip words missing a vocabulary_progress row.\n\n2. Backend router — add `GET /api/vocabulary/leeches?limit=10` in `app/routers/vocabulary.py` returning `{ leeches: [...] }`. Also extend the existing per-word progress update path (where incorrect_count is incremented) with no logic change — just verify it still works. No new POST needed; reuse existing progress update endpoint when the user drills a leech word.\n\n3. Frontend component — create `frontend/src/components/VocabLeechesPanel.tsx`. Collapsible card titled '🪤 Leech Words — words that keep tripping you up'. Shows up to 5 leeches with: word (large), meaning, miss-rate badge (e.g. '4/5 wrong'), 🔊 button to TTS-pronounce the word (use existing speechSynthesis util), and a 'Drill' button. Drill mode shows the meaning + audio and asks the user to type the word (spelling recall — harder than multiple choice, well-suited for stubborn words). On submit, compare case-insensitively; call existing vocabulary progress update endpoint with correct/incorrect to update SRS. Show ✓/✗ feedback inline; auto-advance to next leech. After all 5 done, show a summary ('You drilled 5 leeches — 3 correct! Come back tomorrow to reinforce.'). Empty state: 'No leech words yet. Keep practicing — we surface words you miss 3+ times here.'\n\n4. Wire into `frontend/src/pages/Vocabulary.tsx` — render `<VocabLeechesPanel />` above the existing SRS progress card (only if leeches array non-empty, otherwise render collapsed empty state). Fetch on mount and after any drill round completes.\n\n5. API client — add `fetchVocabLeeches(limit?: number)` in `frontend/src/api.ts`.\n\nWhy: addresses an under-touched area (Vocabulary SRS / progress per the priority hint), targets a real learning pain (leech words are a known SRS problem), provides immediate UI value with focused drill mechanics (echoing recent successful drill features like #660, #665), and requires no schema migration since incorrect_count/correct_count already exist.\n\nTesting: unit test `get_leech_words` in `tests/unit/` covering (a) word with 4 incorrect / 1 correct surfaces, (b) word with 3 correct / 1 incorrect does NOT surface, (c) ordering by miss_rate, (d) limit honored, (e) words without progress row excluded.",
