{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Reduced Forms drill: hear connected speech, expand it, then shadow the reduction",
  "description": "Add a new short practice tile 'Reduced Forms' that trains learners on the gap between written English and natural connected speech (gonna/wanna/gotta/hafta/lemme/dunno/'d've/coulda/shoulda, t-flapping, schwa reductions like 'fer' for 'for'). Each round (5 items) has three steps: (1) Listen — TTS plays a short utterance using the reduced form (e.g., 'I'm gonna grab a coffee, wanna come?'). (2) Expand — user types or selects the full/citation form ('I am going to grab a coffee, do you want to come?'); answer is graded by normalized string match against the canonical full form (case/punct insensitive, allow contractions like I'm/I am). (3) Shadow — user records themselves saying the reduced version; reuse existing pronunciation scoring (app/routers/pronunciation.py) to give an accuracy score and highlight which reduced chunk was/wasn't produced. Show a results screen with per-item accuracy and a 'reductions learned today' list saved to a new table.\n\nBackend: new router app/routers/reduced_forms.py with endpoints GET /api/reduced-forms/round (returns 5 items: id, reduced_text, full_text, audio via existing TTS, focus_chunks list like ['gonna','wanna']) and POST /api/reduced-forms/attempt {item_id, expand_correct, shadow_score}. Item generation: curated seed list of ~40 items in app/dal/reduced_forms.py grouped by reduction type (going_to, want_to, have_to, have_contractions, t_flap, schwa_function_words); round samples by user weakness (least-correct type first, falling back to random). Persist attempts in new table reduced_form_attempts(id INTEGER PK, item_id TEXT, reduction_type TEXT, expand_correct INTEGER, shadow_score REAL, created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP). Add to database.py SCHEMA AND to _MIGRATIONS:\n  'CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reduced_form_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, reduction_type TEXT NOT NULL, expand_correct INTEGER NOT NULL, shadow_score REAL, created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)'\n(table creation is idempotent so a single CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS migration entry is sufficient — no ALTER needed since this is a brand-new table).\n\nFrontend: new component frontend/src/components/ReducedFormsDrill.tsx with the three-step flow (Listen → Expand input → Shadow record), progress dots for 5 items, end-of-round summary showing reductions practiced and weakest type. Add a tile/entry on the home page (frontend/src/components/Home.tsx or equivalent) labeled 'Reduced Forms' next to existing warmup/shadowing tiles. Reuse existing TTS playback hook and pronunciation recording component used by ShadowingMissedWords.\n\nWhy: complements the recently added pace-match, minimal pairs, and pronunciation heatmap by attacking the #1 listening-comprehension blocker for intermediate learners — failing to recognize reduced/connected speech — and pairs comprehension with production in one ~2-minute session.",
