{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Power Word Challenge: target SRS vocab during conversation",
  "description": "Add a learner-facing 'Power Word Challenge' to the Conversation feature that ties spaced-repetition vocabulary review to live conversation practice. At conversation start, the backend selects 2–3 due/learning vocabulary words from the user's SRS deck (via existing vocabulary DAL) and returns them as `target_words` in the StartResponse. As the user sends messages, the backend detects which target words appear (case-insensitive, whole-word match using a regex with word boundaries; also accept simple morphological variants by stemming trailing 's', 'es', 'ed', 'ing') and persists per-word usage flags. The frontend displays a small 'Target words to use' panel above the conversation input with each word as a chip that turns green with a check when used. The end-of-conversation summary lists which targets were used, and for each used word the SRS level is bumped via `vocab_dal.update_progress(correct=True)` (no penalty for unused words). \n\nImplementation:\n1. `app/database.py`: add `target_words TEXT` (JSON array of {word, used:bool}) to `conversations`. Add migration: `_MIGRATIONS.append(\"ALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN target_words TEXT\")`.\n2. `app/dal/conversation.py`: extend `create_conversation` to accept and store `target_words`; add `get_target_words(db, conversation_id)`, `mark_target_used(db, conversation_id, word)` helpers that read/write the JSON column atomically.\n3. `app/dal/vocabulary.py`: add `pick_target_words(db, limit=3)` that returns up to N due word strings (preferring level 1–4 words from `get_due_word_ids` ordered by next_review_at; falls back to recently-saved words if none due). Pure addition, no schema change.\n4. `app/routers/conversation.py`:\n   - In `/start`, call `pick_target_words`, persist via `create_conversation`, return `target_words: [{word, used}]` in StartResponse (add field to Pydantic model).\n   - In `/message`, after saving the user turn, scan `req.content` for any target word (regex `\\b(word|words|word(ed|ing))\\b` case-insensitive). For each newly-used target, call `mark_target_used` and `vocab_dal.update_progress(word, correct=True)`. Include updated `target_words` array in the MessageResponse so the UI can update chips.\n   - In `/end` summary response, include `target_words_used: [...]` and `target_words_unused: [...]`.\n5. `frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx`: render a `TargetWordsPanel` chip row above the input. Each chip shows the word; when used, add a check icon and a green/success class. Show a celebratory toast when all targets are used. Display in summary view too.\n6. Add `tests/integration/test_conversation_target_words.py` covering: target_words present in /start response when due words exist; absent (empty list) when none; usage detection with exact match, capitalization, and 'running' matching 'run'; SRS level bump on use; no double-credit when same word used twice; summary contains used/unused split.\n\nKeeps a single LLM-call structure (no extra latency on /message — pure regex), ties two existing features together, and produces visible learner progress.",
