{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Add Vocabulary Spelling Challenge mode (TTS dictation of saved words)",
  "description": "Add a new 'Spelling Challenge' practice mode within the Vocabulary page that combines listening and recall: TTS speaks a word from the user's saved vocabulary bank, and the user must type the correct spelling. This fills a real gap — currently vocabulary practice tests recognition (multiple-choice) and meaning recall (cloze), but never spelling/listening of the target word itself.\n\nBackend (`app/routers/vocabulary.py`):\n1. Add `GET /api/vocabulary/spelling-challenge?topic=...&limit=10` that selects up to N words from `vocabulary_progress` for the topic (preferring due/leech words via existing `get_due_word_ids` logic with fallback to recently-saved words). Returns a list of items: `{id, word, meaning, example_sentence, difficulty}`. The `word` field is needed server-side for grading; for security simply return it (this app is local/single-user — same pattern used by quiz endpoint).\n2. Add `POST /api/vocabulary/spelling-challenge/answer` accepting `{word_id, typed: str}`. Normalize (trim, lowercase, collapse internal whitespace) and compare against stored `word`. Compute Levenshtein distance for partial-credit feedback (`exact | close (<=2 edits) | wrong`). Reuse `vocab_dal.update_progress(word_id, is_correct)` where `is_correct = (result == 'exact')`. Response: `{word_id, result, correct_word, distance, new_level}`.\n3. No schema changes required — reuses `vocabulary_progress` table.\n\nFrontend (`frontend/src/pages/VocabularyPage.tsx` + new `frontend/src/components/SpellingChallenge.tsx`):\n1. Add a 'Spelling Challenge' card/button to the vocabulary page that opens the new component.\n2. Component flow: per question, auto-play TTS (reuse existing `speak()` util / Web Speech API used elsewhere in the app) showing only the meaning as a hint, with a Replay (▶) button (counts replays — show count, no penalty), a text input, and Submit. After submit, show feedback: green for exact, amber for close (display correct spelling with diff highlighting of misspelled letters), red for wrong. Show running score and progress (e.g., 3/10).\n3. Final results screen showing correct count, words missed (with replay buttons to hear again), and a 'Retry missed' button that runs only the wrong/close ones again.\n4. Mobile-friendly: large input, autoFocus, Enter submits, no autocorrect/autocapitalize/spellcheck attributes on the input.\n\nTests:\n- `tests/unit/test_vocabulary_dal.py` (or new `test_spelling_challenge.py`): test normalization + distance grading function (exact/close/wrong boundaries) and that `update_progress` is called with correct `is_correct` only on exact match.\n- `tests/integration/test_vocabulary_api.py`: integration test for both new endpoints — empty vocabulary returns empty list; submit exact match advances SRS level; submit typo within 2 edits returns `close` and does NOT advance level.",
