{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "PERF-HIGH: Trim /message prompt + first-token latency badge to cut conversation reply lag",
  "description": "Backlog item PERF-HIGH (Conversation 応答が遅い ~15s). Streaming SSE and parallel grammar+reply are already implemented, so the next high-leverage lever is prompt-size reduction in /api/conversation/message and /message/stream — long histories (16 turns of full text) plus appended memory facts inflate every round-trip. This change shortens the LLM context AND surfaces measured first-token latency to the user so the perf win is visible.\n\nBackend (app/routers/conversation.py + app/dal/conversation.py):\n1. Reduce MESSAGE_HISTORY_MAX_TURNS from 16 → 10 in app/routers/conversation.py.\n2. In app/dal/conversation.py `format_history_text`, add a `max_chars_per_message: int = 240` parameter; when a single message exceeds it, truncate to first 200 chars + ' …' (preserving role tag). This caps tail growth even when 10 turns include long assistant replies. When older turns are dropped, prepend a single line `[Earlier turns omitted: N messages]` so the model still knows context was elided.\n3. Move the memory-facts injection (CONVERSATION_MEMORY_KEY block, lines ~722-733 and ~872-883) into a small helper `_append_memory_facts(system: str, raw: str|None) -> str` that caps facts at 6 (currently 10) and per-fact char length at 120. Call it from both /message and /message/stream so the two code paths stay identical.\n4. In stream_message event_gen(), emit a new SSE event `{\"type\":\"first_chunk\",\"latency_ms\":<int>}` immediately before yielding the very first non-empty chunk (measure with time.monotonic() captured before stream_chat). This gives the frontend an actionable metric and replaces vague \"reply slow\" complaints with a number.\n5. Add structured log `logger.info(\"send_message timings prompt_chars=%d history_turns=%d total_ms=%d\", ...)` at the end of /message and /message/stream so p50 can be measured from logs.\n\nFrontend (frontend/src/api.ts + frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx):\n6. In api.ts `streamMessage`, add `onFirstChunk?: (latencyMs: number) => void` handler, parse the new `first_chunk` SSE event, and invoke it.\n7. In Conversation.tsx, add a tiny inline badge next to the streaming assistant bubble showing `⚡ {latencyMs}ms to first word` once received. Style: subtle text-xs muted color, fades after 4s. This tells the user the AI is actually responding quickly even if the full reply takes longer, and lets us A/B perceive perf.\n\nTests (tests/unit/test_conversation_dal.py):\n8. Add tests for the new `format_history_text(max_chars_per_message=...)` truncation: long message gets `…` suffix; short messages untouched; older-turn elision marker appears when total turns > max_turns.\n\nNo schema changes. No config.yaml changes. All changes are backward-compatible (new SSE event is additive; api.ts handler is optional). Estimated p50 reduction: ~15-25% on long (8+ turn) conversations from prompt shrink, plus large perceived UX win from the latency badge.",
